<%# One collision toast, appended into the #toasts container via Turbo Streams.
    The container (in show.html.erb) is the fixed, bottom-right flex column that
    stacks these; each toast just needs a unique DOM id and its styling. The
    fade-in + auto-dismiss is pure CSS (toast-fade/toast-collapse keyframes in the
    Tailwind build) — no JS controller. `toast` is a hash with :id and :message. %>
<div id="toast_<%= toast.fetch(:id) %>"
     class="game-toast w-[346px] max-w-[90vw] border-[3px] border-ink rounded-[3px] bg-totp text-white px-3.5 py-3 font-bold shadow-brut pointer-events-none">
  ↯ <%= toast.fetch(:message) %>
</div>
